<br>
Anyone know what causes that? Usually happens if I have just stopped moving; can get around it by waiting a second or two - but thats not ideal in a scenario where I have some mobs on me already (and I'm trying to root/mez/etc them [moving around to loose aggro to melee types et al])<br>
<br>
On a different (albeit related) note: to decrease spells being interuppted by being hit: how much do you all put in, say, AC items to decrease ur spells being interupted (ie: Higher AC = less hits = less interupts) or do you focus on [somehow?] improving channeling (which seems to be max'd for my level usually anyhow)? Or is there another strategy/way that works well?  I'm finding it hard to get off any spells during melee (PBStuns, roots, mez'es; anything)... Color flux, even when it lands, doesnt seem to give much time to cast root or something (esspecially when my only change fails cuz of interupt prob stated at the begining of post occurs).<br>
<br>
Whew - long question(s).  Thanks in advance for any advice you can give a &lt;Lvl 20 'chanter,<br>
Fiz<br>
