<br>
A couple tips on using Color spells.   Untill you start routinely facing mobs over level 55, those are awesome spells.  However, there is a timing twist to using lvl 4 Color Flux.  Lets say you want to Mez a mob, and lead off with Flux.<br>
<br>
Stun from Color Flux lasts 4 seconds.<br>
It takes 2.25 seconds for your spell gems to refresh.<br>
It takes 2.5 seconds to cast mez.<br>
Togeather, that's 4.75 seconds.  However, Flux wears off in 4 seconds, and mob will immediately swing at you again, likely interrupting you.<br>
Solution: the moment Flux hits, back away from the mob.  As soon as you see your spell gems lighting up again, stop.  When they fully light up, start casting mez.   When the stun wears off, mob will first have to cover the distance you put in between.  Since you had about 2 seconds to backup, it'll take mob more than 0.75 seconds to reach you - in which time your mez will complete.<br>
<br>
